data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your expression-tree code **won't compile** because the overload now accepts a plain lambda. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more manual `Expression.Call`/`Expression.Lambda` construction needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two sub-changes:**

- **Uniquification**: `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one column silently (data corruption risk). Now EF appends a number (e.g., `Street`, `Street1`). If you have an existing database and want to **keep the old shared column**, pin it explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

- **Nested path**: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`. Now it maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (full path). To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> **Important**: If you have existing migrations/databases, either pin column names with `HasColumnName` or generate a new migration and verify the rename is safe.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (supports constant-redaction in logs). Update:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Apply the same `string logCommandText` addition to any other methods you implement (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
